1
00:00:03,737 --> 00:00:05,548
<i>According to
Elisabeth Kubler-Ross,</i>

2
00:00:05,572 --> 00:00:09,441
<i>when we are dying or have
suffered a catastrophic loss,</i>

3
00:00:09,543 --> 00:00:12,378
<i>we all move through
five distinct stages of grief.</i>

4
00:00:12,480 --> 00:00:15,130
<i>We go into denial.</i>

5
00:00:15,232 --> 00:00:16,514
Push another amp...

6
00:00:16,616 --> 00:00:18,678
<i>Because the loss
is so unthinkable</i>

7
00:00:18,702 --> 00:00:20,836
<i>we can't imagine it's true.</i>

8
00:00:20,938 --> 00:00:22,738
Clear!

9
00:00:22,839 --> 00:00:24,839
<i>We become angry with everyone,</i>

10
00:00:24,941 --> 00:00:29,294
<i>angry with survivors, angry
with ourselves, then we bargain.</i>

11
00:00:29,396 --> 00:00:32,697
Damn, O'Malley,
come on. Live, just live.

12
00:00:32,799 --> 00:00:33,882
His ICP's 30.

13
00:00:33,984 --> 00:00:35,662
Push 70 of Mannitol,
start bagging.

14
00:00:35,686 --> 00:00:37,119
His brainstem.

15
00:00:37,220 --> 00:00:42,341
<i>We beg, we plead. We
offer everything we have.</i>

16
00:00:42,443 --> 00:00:47,780
<i>We offer up our souls, in
exchange for just one more day.</i>

17
00:00:50,334 --> 00:00:53,468
Stevens! Can you hear me?

18
00:00:55,255 --> 00:00:56,872
Look at me, Stevens.

19
00:00:59,076 --> 00:01:00,692
Damn it.

20
00:01:03,196 --> 00:01:04,996
<i>When the bargaining has failed,</i>

21
00:01:05,098 --> 00:01:07,399
<i>and the anger is
too hard to maintain,</i>

22
00:01:07,501 --> 00:01:11,269
<i>we fall into
depression, despair,</i>

23
00:01:11,371 --> 00:01:16,625
<i>until finally we have to accept that
we have done everything we can.</i>

24
00:01:16,726 --> 00:01:18,877
<i>We let go.</i>

25
00:01:19,896 --> 00:01:23,464
<i>We let go and move
into acceptance.</i>

26
00:01:28,622 --> 00:01:30,722
Anybody know if he's a donor?

27
00:01:38,165 --> 00:01:39,445
Oh, God!

28
00:01:46,423 --> 00:01:48,840
Whoa, whoa. She wants
it out. Can we take it out?

29
00:01:48,942 --> 00:01:51,977
- She's breathing over the vent.
- Let's pull out the tube.

30
00:01:53,980 --> 00:01:55,880
Dr. Bailey.

31
00:02:01,972 --> 00:02:06,107
Slow down. It's OK, slow down.

32
00:02:21,174 --> 00:02:24,476
His ICP went through the
roof. We did everything.

33
00:02:25,212 --> 00:02:26,578
Everything.

34
00:02:26,680 --> 00:02:29,864
Chief, his organs are viable
for now, but it won't be long

35
00:02:29,966 --> 00:02:32,867
until he's acidotic
and hypothermic.

36
00:02:33,937 --> 00:02:35,336
Is he a donor?

37
00:02:39,410 --> 00:02:42,294
Um... I don't know.

38
00:02:42,396 --> 00:02:44,579
I called his mother.
She's on her way.

39
00:02:44,681 --> 00:02:48,483
Let's close him up and get him to
the ICU in case she wants to see him.

40
00:02:58,996 --> 00:03:01,046
- Who's George?
- What?

41
00:03:01,148 --> 00:03:03,977
John Doe, the guy who threw me
out of the way of the bus, saved my life.

42
00:03:04,001 --> 00:03:08,403
Everyone's crying and saying,
"John Doe is George." Who's George?

43
00:03:12,609 --> 00:03:14,242
- You can't tell her.
- Alex.

44
00:03:14,344 --> 00:03:17,295
She coded in my arms.
Out of nowhere, she died.

45
00:03:17,931 --> 00:03:20,481
Just... I'll tell her.

46
00:03:20,583 --> 00:03:22,967
I'll tell her when
she gets stronger.

47
00:03:23,771 --> 00:03:25,286
Alex.

48
00:03:29,476 --> 00:03:31,092
You OK?

49
00:03:31,928 --> 00:03:35,463
I had... a dream.

50
00:03:37,167 --> 00:03:40,501
- He was in his uniform.
- What?

51
00:03:40,603 --> 00:03:43,738
George is gonna die in the
Army if we don't stop him.

52
00:03:45,074 --> 00:03:47,892
Hand me my phone.
I need my phone.

53
00:04:03,560 --> 00:04:06,394
Who said that was George?
Why do we think that's George?

54
00:04:06,496 --> 00:04:08,463
Meredith said...

55
00:04:09,733 --> 00:04:11,432
I don't know.

56
00:04:14,504 --> 00:04:16,054
That's not George.

57
00:04:19,042 --> 00:04:22,009
Look at his feet,
look how tall he is.

58
00:04:22,846 --> 00:04:24,963
That's not George.

59
00:04:33,407 --> 00:04:34,906
He wrote in my hand.

60
00:04:35,008 --> 00:04:37,609
- What do you mean he wrote?
- What did he do?

61
00:04:37,711 --> 00:04:41,479
He grabbed my hand and squeezed
it and he wrote with his finger.

62
00:04:41,581 --> 00:04:44,799
- Wrote with his finger?
- In my hand, he wrote
"Double O Seven."

63
00:04:46,370 --> 00:04:48,036
Well, give...

64
00:04:50,323 --> 00:04:53,225
- OK, what'd I write?
- "Joe."

65
00:04:53,327 --> 00:04:56,510
- No! No, I did not write "Joe"!
- Are you serious?

66
00:04:56,630 --> 00:04:58,892
- You mean this
may not be O'Malley?
- This is funny.

67
00:04:58,916 --> 00:05:01,883
Did anyone try and call O'Malley?
Can we get him on the phone?

68
00:05:01,985 --> 00:05:04,152
I'm telling you, he
squeezed my hand.

69
00:05:04,254 --> 00:05:06,174
Shut it. You don't
get to talk anymore,

70
00:05:06,223 --> 00:05:07,683
you don't get to
talk ever again.

71
00:05:07,707 --> 00:05:08,802
I could've sworn it was George.

72
00:05:08,826 --> 00:05:10,670
- I got voicemail.
- He's not answering.

73
00:05:10,694 --> 00:05:12,205
He has a freckle
in his right hand,

74
00:05:12,229 --> 00:05:13,728
it's shaped like Texas.

75
00:05:13,830 --> 00:05:15,797
I used to tease him about it.

76
00:05:16,666 --> 00:05:18,199
I'll check.

77
00:06:00,777 --> 00:06:02,343
You people, answer your pages.

78
00:06:07,217 --> 00:06:09,684
George O'Malley jumped
in front of a bus today.

79
00:06:09,786 --> 00:06:13,021
He knew what he was
doing and he did it anyway,

80
00:06:13,123 --> 00:06:15,223
and he did it to save a life.

81
00:06:15,325 --> 00:06:18,410
So I'm not gonna allow
you doctors to stand here.

82
00:06:18,512 --> 00:06:22,914
There are lives on the line,
there are lives we can save.

83
00:06:23,016 --> 00:06:25,917
So if George O'Malley
can jump in front of a bus...

84
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:29,020
we can answer our damn pages.

85
00:06:29,907 --> 00:06:31,656
So let's go.

86
00:06:49,225 --> 00:06:52,244
Damn it. Damn it, O'Malley.

87
00:06:57,384 --> 00:06:59,424
How long ago did the pain start?

88
00:06:59,486 --> 00:07:01,519
I don't know. A few weeks.

89
00:07:01,622 --> 00:07:02,954
Growing pains.

90
00:07:03,056 --> 00:07:05,873
I took him to see our
doctor. He's a bad doctor.

91
00:07:05,975 --> 00:07:08,376
He stands there texting
while I'm talking to him.

92
00:07:08,478 --> 00:07:11,045
He diagnosed Andy
with growing pains.

93
00:07:11,147 --> 00:07:13,014
You know, I grew
up, and growing pains

94
00:07:13,116 --> 00:07:15,233
did not cause me to fall
down on the soccer field.

95
00:07:15,335 --> 00:07:16,812
Mom, you're being
a little dramatic.

96
00:07:16,836 --> 00:07:19,420
Your pain is
dramatic to me, Andy.

97
00:07:19,522 --> 00:07:21,807
Your mom's right. It's a
good thing that you came.

98
00:07:21,909 --> 00:07:25,493
OK. Thanks,
because it does hurt.

99
00:07:25,595 --> 00:07:26,978
Everything hurts, all the time.

100
00:07:27,080 --> 00:07:28,758
OK. I'm gonna give
you a quick exam.

101
00:07:28,782 --> 00:07:30,862
Let me know if the
pain gets worse.

102
00:07:36,023 --> 00:07:37,756
This doesn't feel real.

103
00:07:37,858 --> 00:07:42,110
- Does this feel real to you?
- No. I don't know.

104
00:07:44,998 --> 00:07:46,414
Oh, crap.

105
00:07:46,516 --> 00:07:49,316
I don't want... I can't.

106
00:07:49,419 --> 00:07:53,321
Uh-uh. Don't look away, now.
Come on, you can walk over to her.

107
00:07:55,659 --> 00:07:59,377
- Mrs. O'Malley, I'm so sorry.
- You were his wife.

108
00:07:59,479 --> 00:08:02,580
In God's eyes
you're still his wife.

109
00:08:02,682 --> 00:08:05,066
You should decide about
his organs. You decide.

110
00:08:05,168 --> 00:08:07,713
- But... Uh, um...
- I can't do it, Callie.

111
00:08:07,737 --> 00:08:10,272
I can't do it. You understand?

112
00:08:10,374 --> 00:08:14,643
Ronnie and Jerry are off on
some fishing expedition in Alaska,

113
00:08:14,745 --> 00:08:18,813
and they're gonna come home
and I have to tell them that Georgie...

114
00:08:18,915 --> 00:08:21,666
That's all I can
do. It's all I can...

115
00:08:21,768 --> 00:08:23,501
I can't.

116
00:08:23,603 --> 00:08:28,039
I... I can't even see
him like this, I can't.

117
00:08:28,141 --> 00:08:32,961
You need to do this for
me. Can you do this for me?

118
00:08:50,397 --> 00:08:52,613
Speedboat accident,
19-year-old female.

119
00:08:52,715 --> 00:08:55,183
Lost vitals twice, but
BP's holding in the low 80s.

120
00:08:55,285 --> 00:08:56,846
Both arms amputated
at the scene,

121
00:08:56,870 --> 00:08:58,298
right leg's hanging
on by a thread.

122
00:08:58,322 --> 00:08:59,598
You recover either of the arms?

123
00:08:59,622 --> 00:09:01,450
Probably at the
bottom of Puget Sound.

124
00:09:01,474 --> 00:09:03,753
She was thrown from the boat
and got pulled into the propellers.

125
00:09:03,777 --> 00:09:05,054
She needs more
access, bleeding out.

126
00:09:05,078 --> 00:09:06,578
Get a central line
in her. Let's go!

127
00:09:06,680 --> 00:09:09,425
Type and cross her and get
as much O-neg as possible.

128
00:09:09,449 --> 00:09:11,583
Wait! I found them!

129
00:09:11,685 --> 00:09:13,350
I found them! Her arms!

130
00:09:13,453 --> 00:09:15,470
They were on the boat with her.

131
00:09:15,572 --> 00:09:17,856
I found them in the water.
You have to take them.

132
00:09:19,642 --> 00:09:21,542
They were just
floating in the water.

133
00:09:21,644 --> 00:09:23,189
You can sew them back on, right?

134
00:09:23,213 --> 00:09:24,612
We'll do everything we can.

135
00:09:25,315 --> 00:09:26,814
Oh, my God, Jojo.

136
00:09:26,916 --> 00:09:28,499
That was so gross.

137
00:09:28,602 --> 00:09:30,413
Jasmine, you
just saved her life.

138
00:09:30,437 --> 00:09:32,070
You think?

139
00:09:34,791 --> 00:09:38,743
I'm so sorry. I just heard.
I don't know what to say.

140
00:09:38,845 --> 00:09:41,029
Go home. You need to go home.

141
00:09:41,131 --> 00:09:44,432
You need to cry
and scream and...

142
00:09:44,534 --> 00:09:47,018
When my brother
died I ate donuts.

143
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:49,401
I ate a lot of donuts and
that helped some, but...

144
00:09:49,439 --> 00:09:52,473
God, I don't know what to say.

145
00:09:52,575 --> 00:09:55,060
His mom wants me to
decide about his organs.

146
00:09:55,162 --> 00:09:56,811
He lost his wallet
in the accident.

147
00:09:56,913 --> 00:09:59,713
They don't know if he's a donor.
His mom wants me to decide.

148
00:09:59,815 --> 00:10:04,035
I can't. I can't tell her
no, but I can't decide.

149
00:10:04,137 --> 00:10:06,120
I mean, we were only
married for a few months...

150
00:10:06,223 --> 00:10:09,490
OK, but during those months,

151
00:10:09,592 --> 00:10:12,710
you were the most important
person in George's life.

152
00:10:14,681 --> 00:10:16,181
No.

153
00:10:17,450 --> 00:10:18,916
No, I wasn't.

154
00:10:22,088 --> 00:10:24,272
I'm sorry. OK, so let's
take a look at the X-rays.

155
00:10:24,374 --> 00:10:26,686
Do I need to take my
son to another hospital?

156
00:10:26,710 --> 00:10:27,858
What?

157
00:10:27,960 --> 00:10:30,211
That doctor's hands are shaking

158
00:10:30,313 --> 00:10:32,275
as he tries to stick
my son with a needle,

159
00:10:32,299 --> 00:10:34,332
and those nurses are crying.

160
00:10:34,434 --> 00:10:37,035
You and your friend... What
the hell is going on here?

161
00:10:37,137 --> 00:10:39,487
There was an accident,
and one of our people died.

162
00:10:45,245 --> 00:10:49,514
Andy is my person.
He's my only person,

163
00:10:49,616 --> 00:10:52,517
and something is wrong with him.

164
00:10:52,619 --> 00:10:57,037
So what I'm asking you is, do I
need to take him somewhere else?

165
00:10:57,140 --> 00:11:00,241
No. No.

166
00:11:01,711 --> 00:11:06,831
I'll make Andy my person, OK?
I'll make Andy my person too.

167
00:11:10,821 --> 00:11:12,586
- I didn't tell her, OK?
- Karev.

168
00:11:12,688 --> 00:11:14,322
Look, we just ignored her DNR.

169
00:11:14,424 --> 00:11:17,875
Her kidneys quit and she
coded. She was freakin' intubated!

170
00:11:17,977 --> 00:11:19,027
She's not strong enough.

171
00:11:19,129 --> 00:11:21,278
- What's her BUN?
- Fifteen.

172
00:11:21,381 --> 00:11:23,981
- And her creatinine?
- One-point-five.

173
00:11:24,083 --> 00:11:26,362
She's strong enough.
You have to tell her.

174
00:11:26,386 --> 00:11:28,887
- Why? It can wait.
- No, it can't!

175
00:11:28,989 --> 00:11:31,690
It can't wait because George's
organs won't be viable for long.

176
00:11:31,792 --> 00:11:35,120
If they want to use them, they
have to do it soon. I have to decide,

177
00:11:35,144 --> 00:11:38,979
and I need Izzie to help me because
she's the one who should decide.

178
00:11:39,766 --> 00:11:42,233
She's who should decide.

179
00:11:42,335 --> 00:11:45,970
So that's one reason, and
the other reason is, Karev,

180
00:11:46,073 --> 00:11:49,774
if you let them unplug George without
giving her a chance to say goodbye...

181
00:11:49,876 --> 00:11:52,309
I mean it, she will
never forgive you.

182
00:11:52,411 --> 00:11:54,311
You have to tell her.

183
00:12:00,019 --> 00:12:02,481
Her pressure keeps dropping.

184
00:12:02,505 --> 00:12:04,483
Throw in an IO, get the
blood in a rapid infuser.

185
00:12:04,507 --> 00:12:07,792
These are pretty clean amputations.
We can reattach these arms.

186
00:12:07,894 --> 00:12:09,911
Yay! I found them, you know.

187
00:12:10,013 --> 00:12:12,480
I'm looking at omentum.
Let's get her to an OR now!

188
00:12:12,582 --> 00:12:14,176
Does your friend
have any allergies,

189
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:16,650
medical condition,
on any medication?

190
00:12:16,752 --> 00:12:18,214
- She's not our friend.
- Jasmine!

191
00:12:18,238 --> 00:12:20,232
We barely know her. We met
her on the plane from Sydney.

192
00:12:20,256 --> 00:12:21,696
We're backpacking,
seeing the States.

193
00:12:21,774 --> 00:12:24,058
We're just traveling mates.

194
00:12:24,160 --> 00:12:25,977
- She's really nice, though.
- Let's move!

195
00:12:26,079 --> 00:12:27,461
Her name, can you give me that?

196
00:12:27,563 --> 00:12:29,408
- Clara.
- Mm-hm. Clara Ferguson,
I think.

197
00:12:29,432 --> 00:12:32,683
- Clara Ferguson.
- Clara, hang in there. Stay with me.

198
00:12:32,786 --> 00:12:35,503
She lives with her mum in London.
I have her backpack in my car.

199
00:12:35,605 --> 00:12:37,249
- OK, get it.
- Should we stay?

200
00:12:37,273 --> 00:12:38,757
Yes. In the waiting room.

201
00:12:38,859 --> 00:12:40,958
I'll update you when I can.

202
00:12:41,060 --> 00:12:42,259
Dr. Shepherd.

203
00:12:43,279 --> 00:12:45,039
Mr. Jennings. It's
good to see you.

204
00:12:45,064 --> 00:12:47,615
- Derek, right? May I call you Derek?
- Of course.

205
00:12:47,717 --> 00:12:50,918
I understand you lost a
resident. It's sad. I'm sorry.

206
00:12:51,020 --> 00:12:53,154
But the hospital
board is meeting soon.

207
00:12:53,256 --> 00:12:56,924
I need to know if you'd like to be the
next chief of surgery at Seattle Grace.

208
00:12:59,829 --> 00:13:02,947
George... it's me.

209
00:13:03,049 --> 00:13:07,368
You know, I pretty much
died not too long ago.

210
00:13:08,171 --> 00:13:10,871
So I need you to call me back.

211
00:13:11,424 --> 00:13:12,857
Please.

212
00:13:18,181 --> 00:13:23,134
I know. I played the cancer
card, I'm gross. Whatever.

213
00:13:24,670 --> 00:13:28,088
I need to tell you something
and I need you to not panic.

214
00:13:28,190 --> 00:13:30,058
I need you to keep breathing.

215
00:13:30,160 --> 00:13:33,794
I need you to
stay alive 'cause...

216
00:13:33,896 --> 00:13:39,083
I swear to God, I need
you to stay alive, all right?

217
00:13:41,003 --> 00:13:42,403
OK.

218
00:13:44,274 --> 00:13:45,973
O'Malley...

219
00:13:46,075 --> 00:13:47,808
he got in an accident.

220
00:13:49,695 --> 00:13:51,262
He's brain dead.

221
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:56,400
I'm sorry, what?

222
00:14:00,439 --> 00:14:02,272
What about his heart?

223
00:14:05,812 --> 00:14:07,078
OK.

224
00:14:08,131 --> 00:14:11,566
His eyes. I know.

225
00:14:11,668 --> 00:14:14,552
Don't want to imagine
him without his eyes.

226
00:14:23,696 --> 00:14:25,563
George would give everything.

227
00:14:27,199 --> 00:14:30,401
His skin, his eyes, he
would give everything.

228
00:14:45,985 --> 00:14:47,118
I have a kid in there.

229
00:14:47,220 --> 00:14:49,520
Fifteen years old,
previously healthy.

230
00:14:49,622 --> 00:14:52,173
Has back pain bad
enough to cause vomiting.

231
00:14:52,275 --> 00:14:53,574
Can you talk it through with me

232
00:14:53,676 --> 00:14:55,509
because I can't
figure out what it is

233
00:14:55,611 --> 00:14:56,910
and I think best out loud.

234
00:14:57,013 --> 00:15:00,298
Did you not hear
about George O'Malley?

235
00:15:02,184 --> 00:15:04,785
I did. It's incredibly sad.

236
00:15:07,590 --> 00:15:12,459
I cannot talk to you right
now. I cannot work right now.

237
00:15:16,783 --> 00:15:20,752
Dr. Bailey, I hear that.

238
00:15:20,853 --> 00:15:22,587
And I don't mean
to be insensitive,

239
00:15:22,689 --> 00:15:25,856
but this kid, this
kid's still alive.

240
00:15:25,958 --> 00:15:28,259
And I don't know what's
wrong with him, not a clue.

241
00:15:28,361 --> 00:15:32,330
So, I need you to work.

242
